{{Infobox storm | name = Bucca tornado | image = Bucca Tornado.jpg | alt = | caption = Bucca Tornado | formed = 29 November 1992 2:30pm [[Time in Australia|EST]] | active = | dissipated = | lowest pressure = | lowest temperature = | tornadoes = | fujitascale = F4 | tornado duration = | highest winds = | gusts = | maximum snow = | power outages = | casualties = None | damages = Unknown | affected = [[Bucca, Queensland|Bucca]], [[Bullyard, Queensland|Bullyard]] | location = | current advisories = | enhanced = | notes = }} The '''Bucca tornado''' was one of the most violent tornadoes ever observed in [[Australia]], being the first Australian tornado to be officially rated F4 on the [[Fujita scale]].<ref>{{cite web |title = Tornadoes |url = http://www.bom.gov.au/lam/climate/levelthree/c20thc/storm1.htm |publisher = Bureau of Meteorology |accessdate = 6 April 2008|archiveurl=http://pandora.nla.gov.au/pan/96122/20090317-1643/www.bom.gov.au/lam/climate/levelthree/c20thc/storm1.html|archivedate=17 March 2009}}</ref> It occurred near the township of [[Bucca, Queensland|Bucca]] (near [[Bundaberg, Queensland|Bundaberg]]) in [[Queensland]] on 29 November 1992 at around 2:20pm [[Time in Australia|AEST]]. The tornado was accompanied by cricket-ball sized hail across Bucca and [[Bullyard]] regions.
The tornado damaged or destroyed nine houses, some flattened to the ground. Trees were snapped and stones were found embedded into tree trunks. Several tree saplings were speared into the walls of homes. A refrigerator from one home was blown away and never found. A 3-ton truck was also thrown {{convert|300|m}} and approximately 20 cattle were killed.<ref>{{cite web|title = Severe Thunder Storms and Bucca Tornado|url = http://hardenup.org/umbraco/customContent/media/596_Gladstone_Tornado_Bucca_1992.pdf|publisher = Harden Up|author = Callaghan, Jeff|work = Bureau of Meteorology|accessdate = 10 February 2012|deadurl = no|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150514004937/http://hardenup.org/umbraco/customContent/media/596_Gladstone_Tornado_Bucca_1992.pdf|archivedate = 14 May 2015|df = }}</ref>
The [[1992 Queensland storms|weather system that spawned]] the Bucca tornado was also responsible for an F3 tornado at [[Oakhurst, Queensland|Oakhurst]].
