Investigations by members of the Italian parliament revealed that '''Bruno Mentasti-Granelli''', who is known as a close friend of Italian Prime Minister [[Silvio Berlusconi]], owns 33 percent of CEIGH through two companies, Hexagon Prima and Hexagon Seconda.<ref name="hexagon">{{citeweb|url=http://www.jamestown.org/single/?no_cache=1&tx_ttnews%5Btt_news%5D=34194|title=Berlusconi, Centrex, Hexagon 1 and 2 and Gazprom|publisher=''[[The Jamestown Foundation]]''|date=2008-12-01}}</ref>

The deal was denounced due to the spreading scandal.<ref>[http://www.kommersant.com/page.asp?id=636565 The Putin and Pals Project]. Kommersant. Dec. 24, 2005</ref> Italian parliament blocked the contract, accusing Berlusconi of having a personal interest in the contract.<ref name="hexagon"/>

[[Robert Nowikovsky]], an Austrian lawyer linked to Russian operations, was one of the company's directors.<ref name="hexagon"/>

