'''Chamicero de Perijá''' is a small [[nature reserve]] in [[Colombia]] established in 2014. It is centered on the Colombian side of the [[Serranía de Perijá]] mountain range, part of the [[Cordillera Oriental (Colombia)|East Andes]].

Chamicero de Perijá protects a {{convert|1850|acre}} area of [[cloud forest]] habitat which is home to several rare bird [[taxon|taxa]], including the [[Perijá thistletail]], the [[Perijá metaltail]], the [[Perijá brush-finch]], an endemic subspecies of the [[rufous antpitta]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Chamicero de Perijá Nature Reserve|url=http://globalwildlife.org/our-work/regions/south-america/chamicero-de-perija-nature-reserve/|publisher=[[Global Wildlife Conservation]]|accessdate= 5 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Rare bird paradise protected in war-torn Colombian mountain range (photos)|publisher=[[Mongabay]]|url=http://news.mongabay.com/2014/07/rare-bird-paradise-protected-in-war-torn-colombian-mountain-range-photos/|date= 22 July 2014|author= Jeremy Hance|accessdate=5 September 2015}}</ref> and the [[Perijá tapaculo]].<ref>{{Cite news|title= Chamicero del Perija ProAves reserve protects new species of Tapaculo|url= http://www.proaves.org/chamicero-del-perija-proaves-reserve-protects-new-species-of-tapaculo/?lang=en|publisher= [[ProAves]]|accessdate= 5 September 2015}}</ref>

