An '''energy minister''' is a position in many [[government]]s responsible for [[energy]] production and regulation, developing governmental energy policy, scientific research, and [[natural resources]] [[conservation ethic|conservation]]. In some countries, environmental responsibilities are given to a separate '''[[environment minister]]'''.
