'''Photoinduced [[phase transition]]''' is a process to the [[nonequilibrium phases]] generated from an equilibrium by shining on high energy [[photons]], and the nonequilibrium phase is a macroscopic excited domain that has new structural and electronic orders quite different from the starting ground state (equilibrium phase).<ref>Nasu, K. (2004). Photoinduced Phase Transitions. World Scientific Publishing Co. Pte. Ltd. {{ISBN|981-238-763-3}}
